    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-17T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >June 17, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 17—10:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed orally by the Foreign Office that an order was issued this morning
                    prohibiting the transit of all cargo to China. It is <pb facs="0034" n="26"
                        xml:id="pg_26"/> rumored that the reason for the order is to retain in
                    Indo-China supplies for defensive purposes or the acceptance of an ultimatum
                    such as that mentioned in my despatch 98 dated June 4<note n="50"
                        xml:id="d37fn50">Not printed; it reported a conversation with Marc
                        Chadourne, a French writer, in which he said he believed it possible that
                        Japan would issue an ultimatum to Indochina to stop all shipments to the
                        Chinese Government (893.00/14558).</note> or a combination of the above.</p>
                <p>Sent to naval radio, Cavite, for repetition to the Department, Chungking,
                    Peiping, Hong Kong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
